      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Online advice is often unreliable, and doubling up on ACE inhibitors like lisinopril can cause a sudden, dangerous drop in your potassium levels or a sharp dip in blood pressure. Your body regulates these levels, and trying to force them back up with an extra pill is risky. For any missed dose, stick to your routine and take the missed dose when you remember, but if you are concerned about the gap, you should immediately consult with your pharmacist or doctor for personalized guidance.",
      "source": "target",
